chnell überprüfen.Das Buch ist geeignet zum Selbststudium und als studienbegleitendes Lehrbuch für BWL Zusatz- und Aufbaustudiengänge. Die Themen werden anhand von folgenden Modulen erläutert: Grundlagen, Strategisches Management, Finanzwesen, Marketing, Personalwesen, Organisation, Logistik, Rechnungswesen.  aInformatively tailored to medical requirements, doctors can acquire the relevant aspects of business management with the assistance of this textbook. The author has designed a learning program which is adapted to a medical environment and which is based on the university curriculum of undergraduate and postgraduate business management courses. Using comprehension questions (solutions in the appendix), readers can quickly test their knowledge.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 4aBWL. 4aBetriebswirtschaft. 4aMedizin. 4aMedizinische Ausbildung. 4aMedizinmanagement. 70(DE-588)4069402-10(DE-627)1061035200(DE-576)209176709aBetriebswirtschaftslehre2gnd 7aMEDICAL / General.2bisacsh  aFinanzwesen.  aGrundlagen.  aLogistik.  aManagement.  aMedical training.  aMedicine.  aOrganisation / Business management.  aPersonalwesen.  aRechnungswesen.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Medicine and Life Sciences 2000 - 2014z9783110637915oZDB-23-GML08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2008z9783110212129oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET SCIENCE TECHNOLOGY AND MEDICINE 2008z9783110209082oZDB-23-DMN0 cprintz978311020112340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311020863440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110208634423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110208634/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LAEC  aEBA_CL_MDPM  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL